Description: Body sherd (mended from three fragments) of North Ionian black-figured pottery amphora; inside reserved; exterior: parts of eight legs of horses or deer to left; maeander band below; back of an animal in lower frieze.
Curator's comments: From same pot as British Museum 1888,0601.460.h, 539.f and Oxford, Ashmolean Museum AN1912.33b.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.964)
